net.proteusframework.cms.component.generator

Class SequentialGenerator<P extends PageElement>

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.cms.component.generator.SequentialGenerator<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type parameter.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Cacheable<P>, Generator<P>, Renderer<P>

    public class SequentialGenerator<P extends PageElement>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Generator<P>
    Generator for a list of ContentElements. All beans are processed; beware of parameter name clashes.

    cms-include.js is included as an NDE by default for AJAX support.

    Author:
    Russ Tennant (russ@proteus.co)

      • getDataSourceTimestamp

        public long getDataSourceTimestamp(CmsRequest<P> request)
        Description copied from interface: Generator
        Get the latest timestamp of the data being used to generate the content. The timestamp should be for the content being generated by the generator. The timestamp should not represent data from other elements in the process chain with the exception of delegates not processed by CMS. This method is guaranteed to be called for every CMS (http / servlet) request.
        Specified by:
        getDataSourceTimestamp in interface Generator<P extends PageElement>
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the timestamp or -1 if unknown.

      • getExpireTime

        public long getExpireTime()
        Description copied from interface: Generator
        Get the expire time of the generated content. This method must never return a negative value. Content generators must always specify a valid expire time.
        Specified by:
        getExpireTime in interface Cacheable<P extends PageElement>
        Specified by:
        getExpireTime in interface Generator<P extends PageElement>
        Returns:
        the expire time in millis or 0 if it expires immediately. Return -1 to indicate that the expire time from this Cacheable shouldn't be used unless otherwise specified.

      • getIdentity

        public java.lang.String getIdentity(CmsRequest<P> request)
        Description copied from interface: Cacheable
        Return a string that uniquely identifies the information needed to generate or influence the content for the response.

        For example, if the response is dependent on a record from the database, an implementor should return a String representing the database key and a timestamp for when the record was last updated.

        Specified by:
        getIdentity in interface Cacheable<P extends PageElement>
        Parameters:
        request - the request.
        Returns:
        the identity of the generated content or null if unknown / unimplemented.

      • getNDEs

        public java.util.List<NDE> getNDEs()
        Get the NDEs needed by the generated content.

        The NDEs should be assembled in the preRenderProcess method. See the class level javadoc for order of method calls. The ProcessChain will gather the NDEs of any Renderers or PageElements that are delegated to.

        You may call this method to add NDEs to the list returned by the generator.
        Specified by:
        getNDEs in interface Renderer<P extends PageElement>
        Returns:
        the NDEs.
